block append variables
  -
    var pageHeader = {
      title: 'Figures',
      description: 'Documentation and examples for displaying related images and text with the figure component in Bootstrap.',
      url: `https://getbootstrap.com/docs/${bootstrapVersion}/content/figures/`,
      linkText: 'Figures on Bootstrap'
    }

mixin figuresDoc
  p Anytime you need to display a piece of contentâ€”like an image with an optional caption, consider using a 
    code &lt;figure&gt;
  p Use the included 
    code .figure
    | , 
    code .figure-img 
    | and 
    code .figure-caption 
    | classes to provide some baseline styles for the HTML5 
    code &lt;figure&gt; 
    | and 
    code &lt;figcaption&gt;
    |  elements. Images in figures have no explicit size, so be sure to add the .img-fluid class to your 
    code &lt;img&gt; 
    | to make it responsive.
  
mixin figures
  figure.figure(style="max-width: 25rem;")
    = '\n'
    img.figure-img.img-fluid.rounded(src=`${CWD}assets/img/generic/3.jpg`, alt='...')
    = '\n'
    figcaption.figure-caption A caption for the above image.
    = '\n'
